speakers:



### Johannes Oos

About the Author:
•	10 years of experience in the solar industry (majorly Europe and East Africa)
•	3 years of experience in Software Development and Artificial Intelligence
•	Presentation @ Geopython 2018 on Classification of Satellite Images
•	Masterthesis on the Estimation of the Potential of Roof Top Solar Systems in Luxemburg
•	Diplomathesis on Measurement and Simulation of a solar pumping station in Egypt
---
abstract:


Using Google Cloud Machine Learning Engine to built a model that help in estimating photovoltaic system design. An end-to-end python based deep learning application.
---
full_description:


The used technologies are python based and include:
MongoDB
tensorflow
Flask
google.cloud python API

A dataset of labelled satellite images is created. 
Several networks are trained and tested on this dataset.
The network is deployed on a production server.

The results of the classification/segmentaion are used to feed python based photovotlaic simulation libaries. The output is displayed and the results (the potential) evaluated.
